Base.Explanation: Remove a specific group membership from an Active Directory group.

ArrayElement.Name: Group name (LDAP)
ArrayElement.Description: The full LDAP name of the group from which the membership must be updated (example: LDAP://DC_A/CN=Students,DC=domain,DC=com). To specify the group, specify one of the following properties: 'Group name (LDAP)', 'Group name (SAM account name)', 'Group object'.

ArrayElement.Name: Group name (SAM account name)
ArrayElement.Description: The group name specified using the SAM account name (example: DOMAIN_A\Group_C). To specify the group, specify one of the following properties: 'Group name (LDAP)', 'Group name (SAM account name)', 'Group object'.

ArrayElement.Name: Group object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing the group. The property is used to identify the group and can only be generated as a variable by a previous script action. To specify the group, specify one of the following properties: 'Group name (LDAP)', 'Group name (SAM account name)', 'Group object'.

ArrayElement.Name: Account name
ArrayElement.Description: The LDAP name of the account from which the groupmembership must be removed (example: LDAP://DC_B/CN=Student1,DC=domain,DC=com). To specify the group member, specify one of the following properties: 'Account name', 'Account object'.

ArrayElement.Name: Account object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing the account from which the groupmembership must be removed. This value can only be generated as a variable by a previous script action. To specify the group member, specify one of the following properties: 'Account name', 'Account object'.
